    "abstractNote": "The town of Shaqlawa, situated in the Erbil Governorate in the Kurdistan region of northern Iraq, is home to an Aramaic-speaking Christian community belonging to the Chaldean denomination. Based on fieldwork that was carried out in Iraq in 2017 and 2019, this paper presents some details about the Neo-Aramaic (NENA) dialect of the Christians of Shaqlawa.",
